Pernil was really good but for $12 (not including the rice) did not seem like a pound. Fried king fish tasted good. My son had a stomachache after eating and I have been nauseous since then. Save yourself the money and disappointment and order somewhere else.

The decor is great but everything else about this place is the worst.  Absurdly large menu yet they were out of multiple items I tried to order.  Ended up ordering a fried pork chop because the rest of my party had already ordered.  It was really thin and really, really dry.  It cut like wood.  The rice was bland.  I love food, I eat anything but I left 80% of my meal.  When we signaled to the waitress we were done she came by about ten minutes later.  It took another ten or so for her to return for our card.  There were only a couple other tables, I don't know what she was doing.  Then it took another ten minutes for her to bring our card back.  They'd charged us 4% for using a card.  I really wanted to like this place.  I'll never go back but I will tell others about my experience.  ¯_(ツ)_/¯

I don't even know why I keep giving this place a chance.  They have horrible food.  The only reason I came here today was because the next door restaurant was closed.   Food always tastes reheated....  the chicken cutlet was over cooked and tasted old. Seemed like the cutlet was just reheated. It was so dry. Told them politely, and they took it back and it looked like they sprinkled water over the cutlet then returned the same one back to us. They didn't even have the decency to cook another one.  Ugh. Horrible.  The fried plantains (tostones) where under done.  The rice with Peas dry, dry, ! Tasted like old rice, not fresh! The only reason they received one star from me is  because they were very polite.  That's all, otherwise no star at all.   Big disappointment ....  I definitely don't recommend this restaurant.
